# MPI Distributed Matrix Multiply

Distributed matrix multiplication implementing core MPI communication
patterns (scatter, broadcast, gather, reduce) using Python multiprocessing.
Includes strong and weak scaling analysis for NSF ACCESS allocation
preparation.

---

## MPI Patterns Implemented

| Pattern   | MPI Equivalent  | Used for                        |
|-----------|-----------------|---------------------------------|
| Scatter   | MPI_Scatter     | Distribute rows of A to workers |
| Broadcast | MPI_Bcast       | Share matrix B with all workers |
| Gather    | MPI_Gather      | Collect results from workers    |
| Reduce    | MPI_Reduce      | Sum partial results             |

---

## Algorithm (1D Row Decomposition)
```
Matrix A (N×N), Matrix B (N×N)

1. Rank 0 generates A and B
2. Scatter rows of A — each rank gets N/P rows
3. Broadcast full B to all ranks
4. Each rank computes: local_result = local_A @ B
5. Gather results back to rank 0
6. Rank 0 assembles full result
7. Verify: assert np.allclose(result, A @ B)
```

