└── README.md
```

---

## Note on Implementation

This project uses Python `multiprocessing` to simulate MPI patterns
on a Windows machine without admin access. The concepts — scatter,
broadcast, gather, reduce, SPMD execution model — are identical to
`mpi4py`. Porting to real MPI on an ACCESS Linux cluster is a
straightforward substitution that would demonstrate the expected
linear scaling behavior described in SCALING_REPORT.md.

---

## Connection to ACCESS Application

This project produces the scaling analysis required in an ACCESS
proposal to demonstrate that submitted code can effectively utilize
parallel HPC resources. Combined with Projects 1 and 2:

- Project 1 (Dask Pipeline) → parallel data infrastructure
- Project 2 (GNN) → scientific ML model justifying GPU hours
- Project 3 (MPI) → HPC readiness and scaling methodology
